<div id="so_formfield_dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_" class="field fld_description fld-ro">

            <div class="label" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__field-label">
	<label for="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_">Synopsis</label><span class="req-indicator"></span>:
      </div>
            
      	 	<div class="widget" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__widget">
			<div class="notice_desc_dates">
				<span class="added">Added: <input type="hidden" name="dnf_class_values[procurement_notice][description][0][added_on]" value="2014-02-13 08:26:39">Feb 13, 2014 8:26 am</span>
					</div>
		BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF WORK: Contractor shall provide all tools, equipment, materials, labor, supervision, personnel and shall do all things necessary that will result in the creation of a safe walking surface and ADA access for visitors and park staff into and around the Dayton Aviation Heritage National Historical Park Wright-Dunbar Interpretive Center, Museum and Administration Areas.<br /><br />
Work will consist of but will not be limited to: - Removing an entrance drive way - Removing cobblestone pavers sidewalks - Removing cracked and heaving walkways - Removing approximately 504 square feet of pavers - Removing approximately 3500 square feet of concrete walkway - Removing a concrete entrance way - Installing 3500 square feet of topsoil and seed/straw covering - Forming and pouring 55 feet of side walk and 15 feet of curb with an ADA flared wheelchair ramp access along with approximately 25 feet of transition - Hauling away and cleaning up all debris<br /><br />
ESTIMATED RANGE: In accordance with FAR Subpart 36.204, the magnitude of this requirement is estimated between $25,000 and $100,000.<br /><br />
LOCATION: Dayton Aviation Heritage National Historical Park, Wright-Dunbar Interpretive Center Complex (WDIC Complex), 16 South Williams Street, Dayton OH 45402.<br /><br />
The anticipated issuance date of the RFP is on or about February 28, 2014 (subject to change). The Period of Performance for this contract is sixty (60) calendar days. Be advised that this requirement may be delayed, cancelled, or revised at any time during process based on decisions related to Department of the Interior (DOI) and National Park Service (NPS) changes.<br /><br />
The RFP will be posted and available for download without charge at FedConnect (https://www.fedconnect.net) on or about February 28, 2014.<br /><br />
This is a SERVICE-DISABLED VETERAN OWNED SMALL BUSINESS SET-ASIDE under NAICS: 238990, the Small Business Size Standard for this NAICS is $14M.<br /><br />
THERE IS NO CHARGE FOR SOLICITATION DOCUMENTS<br /><br />
GENERAL INFORMATION:<br /><br />
THE FOLLOWING REGISTRATIONS SHALL BE COMPLETED BEFORE TIME OF AWARD. Offerors who are not registered are STRONGLY ENCOURAGED to apply for registration immediately upon receipt of this solicitation. DUN AND BRADSTREET NUMBER (DUNs): To be considered for award, contractors must obtain a Dun and Bradstreet Number (DUNs). Contractors may obtain this number at 1(866)705-5711.<br /><br />
SYSTEM FOR AWARD MANAGEMENT (SAM): Federal Acquisition Regulations require that federal contractors register in the System for Award Management (SAM) database at https://www.sam.gov and enter all mandatory information into the system.  Award cannot be made until the contractor has registered.  Bidders are encouraged to ensure that they are registered in SAM prior to submitting their proposal.<br /><br />
THESE REGISTRATIONS SHALL BE COMPLETED BEFORE TIME OF AWARD.<br /><br />
NO HARD COPY DOCUMENTS WILL BE ISSUED. Point of Contact is the Contract Specialist, Robert Sirn, Phone 330-468-2500 X309, FAX 330-468-2507, e-mail: robert_sirn@nps.gov.


